I have a new song released through that new method called streaming. It seems to be available to hear on Spotify, YouTube and places like that. It’s a translation and reworking of an old song ‘Ich Hab’ noch einen Koffer in Berlin’ which was recorded by Marlene Dietrich amongst others. The song may eventually appear on a solo album which will come out next year if I get the necessary material together but…..in the meantime, I’m busy finalising preparations for the release of my album with Amanda Acevedo who did the artwork for this release using a photo and collage idea sourced from my dear friend Peter Milne. In the meantime have a listen to this song….if you like your music slow and sad, like I do #suitcaseinberlin #petermilne @amandacevedo_6 #jpshilo

This week at the One Star Gallery we will be acknowledging Invasion/Colonisation/Estrellia Day - whatever tf you call it. Presenting films on THE contentious DAY itself including the satirical ‘Babakiueria’ and Philip Noyce’s’Backroads’. Then on Friday and Saturday ‘Manganinnie’, set in  Tasmania in 1830 at the time of the Black Line. Bar open from 6pm Films start at 7:30. Must mention we have signed, hardback copies of the Kid Congo Powers book ‘Some New Kind of Kick’ just arrived from the USA and also more stock of his fabulous sunglasses. Also some copies of my just released double vinyl ‘One Man’s Treasure/Two of Diamonds #babakuieria #backroads  #manganinnie #kidcongopowers #somenewkindofkick #onemanstreasure #twoofdiamonds

I did mention 2 posts ago that it was Admin Day. Misha #mishamau is still sleeping on me while I share with some of you who have read this far that a double album of my first two solo albums (non-Serge) has been released through Mute in the UK. It’s the first time Two of Diamonds has found it’s way onto vinyl format and it’s predecessor, One Man’s Treasure, has not been available like this for ages. Copies are to be found in Australia and elsewhere around the globe (I am reliably informed) Special thanks to the kind folk at @rocksteadyrecords for this loving interpretation of the packaging ♥️ Copies will also be available from @onestarlounge when we are open again with a season of art exhibitions #onemanstreasure #twoofdiamonds #mickharvey

Friday 7pm and Saturday 4pm will see special screenings of footage compiled by John Olson about Tony Cohen as part of the HALF DEAF, COMPLETELY MAD exhibition @onestarlounge John & I will be reading from the book of the same name before the screenings and the book is for sale during the exhibition for the special price of just $26. Show runs 15-17 June. Photographs, artworks, artifacts are in the show plus compiled #musicvideoclips and  #grantmclennan with Tony in studio footage by #KitQuarry playing in the back room @blackincbooks #tonycohen #mickharvey #clintonwalker #strangerinastrangeland #outsiderart #melbournemusicscene #northwestmelbourneprecinct #whatsonmelbourne #melbournecitycouncil #badseeds #thebirthdaypartyband

Tomorrow sees the release of the re-recording of ‘Rooms for the Memory’, put together with great energy and dedication by @janegazzo in support of Ollie Olsen in his time of need. Jane is also running a gofundme - Gift for Ollie Olsen. The re-recording of the song Ollie wrote for the film ‘Dogs in Space’ film was originally sung by Michael Hutchence. This version features myself, @adalitax on vocals _matwatson_ on drums and @duffieldandrew on sequencing and keys and has a video (already up at YouTube) made by Richard Lowenstein, the director of ‘Dogs in Space’. The EP features lots of other songs so grab a copy at your local vinyl store and/or give generously to help Ollie as he battles with life’s vicissitudes and vagaries #ollieolsenofficial #roomsforthememory2023 #mickharvey #andrewduffield #adalitasrsen #matwatson #clintonkraus

Today "Phantasmagoria in 2" the fourth and probably last single from our album will be available on all streaming platforms , the full album release has been moved to the 8th of September. The music video  was filmed in Norway after our first shows together! ( with LJ Spruyt's camera) and it was the first thing we filmed together in June 2022.
